how much has been paid in and how well the investments have performed. </p>\n\n<p>Normally, when you retire, you can take some of your pension pot as a tax-free lump sum. You use the rest to buy yourself an income, on which you may pay tax. </p>\n\n<p>Your pension will be smaller if you retire early because:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you&rsquo;ve had fewer years to pay into your pension</li>\n  <li>your pension will need to last longer</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Defined benefit pension schemes</h2>\n<p>These are sometimes called ‘final salary’ or ‘career average’ earnings-related pension schemes.</p>\n\n<p>The amount you get at retirement is based on a number of things, eg your earnings and how long you&rsquo;ve been a member of the scheme. </p>\n\n<p>In most schemes, when you retire you can take some of your pension as a tax-free lump sum. The rest you get as a regular income, on which you might pay tax. </p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re considering early retirement you&rsquo;ll probably get a smaller pension.</p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"State Pension","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Fstate-pension.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes calculating State Pension, eligibility, claiming and deferring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Fstate-pension","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/state-pension"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/retirement-age.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/retirement-age","title":"Retirement age","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:23:19+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api