ervice.direct.gov.uk/en/state-pension-age-calculator/home.asp\" title=\"State Pension age\">State Pension age</a> you stop paying National Insurance. </p>\n\n<h2>Paying tax</h2>\n<p>You only pay Income Tax if your taxable income - including your private pension and State Pension - is more than your <a href=\"/income-tax-rates\" title=\"tax-free allowances\">tax-free allowances</a> (the amount of income you&rsquo;re allowed before you pay tax).</p>\n\n<p>If you think you should be paying tax you must contact HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>). </p>\n\n<p>However, <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> may have already contacted you to help you work out if you should be paying tax at State Pension age. </p>\n\n<p>When you&rsquo;re 65 <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> may also send you an Age-related Personal Allowance form to calculate your age-related <a href=\"/income-tax-rates\" title=\"tax-free allowances\">personal tax allowance</a>. You must fill this in to get any age-related allowances.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re within a month of reaching 65 and you haven&rsquo;t been sent a form, <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kbroker/hmrc/contactus/search.ladv?sr=0&amp;as=1&amp;cs=ISO-8859-1&amp;sc=hmrc&amp;sf=&amp;sm=0&amp;nh=50&amp;ha=34&amp;tx0=49612&amp;fl0=__dsid:&amp;tx1=2037&amp;raction=view\" title=\"contact HMRC\">contact <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>.</a></p>\n\n<p>You can also download the form and the guidance:</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/p161-man.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form P161 Pension Coding form' (PDF, 62KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form P161 Age-related personal allowance’ (PDF, 62KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/p161-helpsheet.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Pension coding form - help and guidance' (PDF, 55KB)\" rel=\"externa